 "cells": [
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "source": [
    "{\n",
    " \"nbformat\": 4,\n",
    " \"nbformat_minor\": 5,\n",
    " \"metadata\": {\n",
    "  \"kernelspec\": {\n",
    "   \"display_name\": \"Python 3\",\n",
    "   \"language\": \"python\",\n",
    "   \"name\": \"python3\"\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  \"language_info\": {\n",
    "   \"name\": \"python\",\n",
    "   \"version\": \"3.11.0\"\n",
    "  }\n",
    " },\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"# Heart Disease Prediction\\n\", \"\\n\", \"**Classification Project 6 of 100** — Predict whether a patient has heart disease from clinical measurements.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"End-to-end workflow: EDA → preprocessing → baseline → LazyPredict → FLAML → top 3 evaluation.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 2. Project Overview\\n\", \"\\n\", \"Heart disease is the leading cause of death globally. Early detection using routinely collected clinical data can save lives by enabling timely intervention.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"In this notebook we build a **binary classifier** that predicts heart disease presence using 13 clinical features (age, cholesterol, blood pressure, chest pain type, etc.) from the UCI Heart Disease dataset.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"**Workflow:**\\n\", \"1. Download & validate the dataset\\n\", \"2. Perform thorough EDA with visualisations\\n\", \"3. Preprocess with sklearn pipelines (split-before-fit, no leakage)\\n\", \"4. Establish baselines (Dummy, LogReg, Random Forest)\\n\", \"5. Benchmark ~30 classifiers with LazyPredict\\n\", \"6. Run FLAML AutoML\\n\", \"7. Select & evaluate the top 3 models with full metrics\\n\", \"8. Analyse errors and extract clinical insights\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 3. Learning Objectives\\n\", \"\\n\", \"By completing this notebook you will learn to:\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. Work with **clinical/medical data** and understand domain-specific features\\n\", \"2. Handle a **small but clean dataset** (~300 rows) with proper cross-validation awareness\\n\", \"3. Distinguish between **nominal** and **ordinal** categorical clinical features\\n\", \"4. Build a **leakage-free** preprocessing pipeline with `ColumnTransformer`\\n\", \"5. Appreciate why **recall** matters most in medical diagnosis (missing disease is dangerous)\\n\", \"6. Use **DummyClassifier** as sanity-check baseline\\n\", \"7. Benchmark with **LazyPredict** and tune with **FLAML**\\n\", \"8. Evaluate with **accuracy, F1, precision, recall, ROC-AUC, PR-AUC, confusion matrix**\\n\", \"9. Extract **clinical insights** about which features predict heart disease\\n\", \"10. Understand **sensitivity vs specificity** tradeoffs in medical screening\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 4. Problem Statement\\n\", \"\\n\", \"> **Given a patient's clinical measurements (age, sex, chest pain type, blood pressure, cholesterol, etc.), predict whether they have heart disease.**\\n\", \"\\n\", \"This is a **binary classification** task. The target is `target` (1 = disease, 0 = no disease). In medical screening, **false negatives** (missing a sick patient) are far costlier than false positives, making **recall** and **sensitivity** critical.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 5. Why This Project Matters\\n\", \"\\n\", \"| Stakeholder | Impact |\\n\", \"|---|---|\\n\", \"| **Cardiologists** | Decision support for risk stratification |\\n\", \"| **Primary care doctors** | Early screening before expensive tests |\\n\", \"| **Patients** | Earlier detection → better outcomes |\\n\", \"| **Hospitals** | Reduce unnecessary catheterisation procedures |\\n\", \"| **ML learners** | Practice medical ML with sensitivity/specificity tradeoffs |\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 6. Dataset Overview\\n\", \"\\n\", \"| Property | Value |\\n\", \"|---|---|\\n\", \"| **Name** | Heart Disease UCI |\\n\", \"| **Source** | UCI ML Repository / Kaggle |\\n\", \"| **Kaggle slug** | `rohitsinghbisht/heart-disease-uci` |\\n\", \"| **Rows** | ~303 |\\n\", \"| **Features** | 13 clinical measurements |\\n\", \"| **Target** | `target` (1 = heart disease, 0 = no disease) |\\n\", \"| **Class balance** | ~54% disease, ~46% no disease (roughly balanced) |\\n\", \"\\n\", \"**Key columns:**\\n\", \"- `age` — age in years\\n\", \"- `sex` — 1 = male, 0 = female\\n\", \"- `cp` — chest pain type (0-3)\\n\", \"- `trestbps` — resting blood pressure (mm Hg)\\n\", \"- `chol` — serum cholesterol (mg/dl)\\n\", \"- `fbs` — fasting blood sugar > 120 mg/dl (1 = true)\\n\", \"- `restecg` — resting ECG results (0-2)\\n\", \"- `thalach` — maximum heart rate achieved\\n\", \"- `exang` — exercise-induced angina (1 = yes)\\n\", \"- `oldpeak` — ST depression induced by exercise\\n\", \"- `slope` — slope of peak exercise ST segment\\n\", \"- `ca` — number of major vessels coloured by fluoroscopy (0-3)\\n\", \"- `thal` — thalassemia type (1 = normal, 2 = fixed defect, 3 = reversible defect)\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 7. Dataset Source and License Notes\\n\", \"\\n\", \"- **Original creators:** Hungarian Institute of Cardiology, University Hospital Zurich, University Hospital Basel, V.A. Medical Center\\n\", \"- **UCI Repository:** https://archive.ics.uci.edu/ml/datasets/heart+disease\\n\", \"- **Kaggle:** https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/rohitsinghbisht/heart-disease-uci\\n\", \"- **License:** CC BY 4.0 — available for educational and research use.\\n\", \"- **Note:** This is the Cleveland subset, the most commonly used portion.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 8. Environment Setup\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"import subprocess, sys, importlib\\n\", \"\\n\", \"for pkg in [\\\"lazypredict\\\", \\\"flaml\\\", \\\"kagglehub\\\"]:\\n\", \"    try:\\n\", \"        importlib.import_module(pkg)\\n\", \"    except ImportError:\\n\", \"        subprocess.check_call([sys.executable, \\\"-m\\\", \\\"pip\\\", \\\"install\\\", \\\"-q\\\", pkg])\\n\", \"\\n\", \"print(\\\"Environment ready.\\\")\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 9. Imports\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"import os, warnings, json, glob\\n\", \"import numpy as np\\n\", \"import pandas as pd\\n\", \"import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\\n\", \"import seaborn as sns\\n\", \"\\n\", \"from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\\n\", \"from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\\n\", \"from sklearn.compose import ColumnTransformer\\n\", \"from sklearn.pipeline import Pipeline\\n\", \"from sklearn.dummy import DummyClassifier\\n\", \"from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression\\n\", \"from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier, GradientBoostingClassifier\\n\", \"from sklearn.metrics import (\\n\", \"    accuracy_score, precision_score, recall_score, f1_score,\\n\", \"    roc_auc_score, average_precision_score,\\n\", \"    ConfusionMatrixDisplay, RocCurveDisplay, PrecisionRecallDisplay,\\n\", \"    classification_report\\n\", \")\\n\", \"\\n\", \"from lazypredict.Supervised import LazyClassifier\\n\", \"from flaml import AutoML\\n\", \"\\n\", \"warnings.filterwarnings(\\\"ignore\\\")\\n\", \"sns.set_theme(style=\\\"whitegrid\\\")\\n\", \"SEED = 42\\n\", \"print(\\\"All imports loaded.\\\")\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 10. Configuration / Constants\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"KAGGLE_SLUG = \\\"rohitsinghbisht/heart-disease-uci\\\"\\n\", \"TARGET = \\\"target\\\"\\n\", \"TEST_SIZE = 0.20\\n\", \"VAL_SIZE = 0.15\\n\", \"SEED = 42\\n\", \"FLAML_BUDGET = 60  # seconds\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Target: {TARGET} | Test: {TEST_SIZE} | Seed: {SEED}\\\")\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 11. Dataset Download or Loading\\n\", \"\\n\", \"We use `kagglehub` to download the dataset. If unavailable, we fall back to the sklearn-bundled version or a direct URL.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"import kagglehub\\n\", \"\\n\", \"try:\\n\", \"    path = kagglehub.dataset_download(KAGGLE_SLUG)\\n\", \"    print(f\\\"Dataset downloaded to: {path}\\\")\\n\", \"    csv_files = glob.glob(os.path.join(path, \\\"**\\\", \\\"*.csv\\\"), recursive=True)\\n\", \"    df_raw = pd.read_csv(csv_files[0])\\n\", \"except Exception as e:\\n\", \"    print(f\\\"Kaggle download failed: {e}\\\")\\n\", \"    print(\\\"Falling back to UCI direct URL...\\\")\\n\", \"    url = \\\"https://archive.ics.uci.edu/ml/machine-learning-databases/heart-disease/processed.cleveland.data\\\"\\n\", \"    col_names = [\\\"age\\\",\\\"sex\\\",\\\"cp\\\",\\\"trestbps\\\",\\\"chol\\\",\\\"fbs\\\",\\\"restecg\\\",\\\"thalach\\\",\\\"exang\\\",\\\"oldpeak\\\",\\\"slope\\\",\\\"ca\\\",\\\"thal\\\",\\\"target\\\"]\\n\", \"    df_raw = pd.read_csv(url, names=col_names, na_values=\\\"?\\\")\\n\", \"    # Binarise target (0 = no disease, 1-4 = disease)\\n\", \"    df_raw[\\\"target\\\"] = (df_raw[\\\"target\\\"] > 0).astype(int)\\n\", \"\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Shape: {df_raw.shape}\\\")\\n\", \"df_raw.head()\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 12. Data Validation Checks\\n\", \"\\n\", \"Verify shape, data types, missing values, duplicates, and target distribution.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"print(f\\\"Shape: {df_raw.shape}\\\")\\n\", \"print(f\\\"\\\\nDtypes:\\\\n{df_raw.dtypes}\\\")\\n\", \"\\n\", \"missing = df_raw.isnull().sum()\\n\", \"print(f\\\"\\\\nMissing values:\\\\n{missing[missing > 0]}\\\")\\n\", \"if missing.sum() == 0:\\n\", \"    print(\\\"No missing values.\\\")\\n\", \"\\n\", \"df = df_raw.copy()\\n\", \"\\n\", \"# Handle missing values in ca and thal if present\\n\", \"for col in [\\\"ca\\\", \\\"thal\\\"]:\\n\", \"    if col in df.columns and df[col].isnull().any():\\n\", \"        df[col] = df[col].fillna(df[col].median())\\n\", \"        print(f\\\"Filled {col} missing with median.\\\")\\n\", \"\\n\", \"# Ensure target is binary\\n\", \"if TARGET in df.columns:\\n\", \"    if df[TARGET].nunique() > 2:\\n\", \"        df[TARGET] = (df[TARGET] > 0).astype(int)\\n\", \"        print(\\\"Binarised target.\\\")\\n\", \"\\n\", \"dupes = df.duplicated().sum()\\n\", \"print(f\\\"\\\\nDuplicate rows: {dupes}\\\")\\n\", \"if dupes > 0:\\n\", \"    df = df.drop_duplicates().reset_index(drop=True)\\n\", \"\\n\", \"print(f\\\"\\\\nTarget distribution:\\\\n{df[TARGET].value_counts()}\\\")\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Disease rate: {df[TARGET].mean():.1%}\\\")\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 13. Exploratory Data Analysis\\n\", \"\\n\", \"We explore feature distributions, correlations, and relationships with heart disease status.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"df.describe().T\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"# Target distribution\\n\", \"fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(5, 4))\\n\", \"df[TARGET].value_counts().plot.bar(ax=ax, color=[\\\"steelblue\\\", \\\"salmon\\\"])\\n\", \"ax.set_title(\\\"Target Distribution\\\")\\n\", \"ax.set_xticklabels([\\\"No Disease\\\", \\\"Disease\\\"], rotation=0)\\n\", \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\", \"plt.show()\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"# Correlation with target\\n\", \"numeric_cols = df.select_dtypes(include=[np.number]).columns.tolist()\\n\", \"corr = df[numeric_cols].corr()[TARGET].drop(TARGET).sort_values(key=abs, ascending=False)\\n\", \"print(\\\"Correlations with target:\\\")\\n\", \"print(corr)\\n\", \"\\n\", \"fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 8))\\n\", \"sns.heatmap(df[numeric_cols].corr(), cmap=\\\"coolwarm\\\", center=0, annot=True, fmt=\\\".2f\\\", ax=ax)\\n\", \"ax.set_title(\\\"Feature Correlation Matrix\\\")\\n\", \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\", \"plt.show()\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"# Key features by disease status\\n\", \"fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 3, figsize=(15, 10))\\n\", \"plot_cols = [\\\"age\\\", \\\"thalach\\\", \\\"oldpeak\\\", \\\"cp\\\", \\\"ca\\\", \\\"thal\\\"]\\n\", \"for ax, col in zip(axes.flat, plot_cols):\\n\", \"    if col in df.columns:\\n\", \"        for label in [0, 1]:\\n\", \"            tag = \\\"Disease\\\" if label == 1 else \\\"No Disease\\\"\\n\", \"            ax.hist(df[df[TARGET]==label][col], bins=20, alpha=0.5, label=tag)\\n\", \"        ax.set_title(col)\\n\", \"        ax.legend()\\n\", \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\", \"plt.show()\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 14. Target Analysis\\n\", \"\\n\", \"The target is roughly balanced (~54% disease, ~46% no disease). This means accuracy is a reasonable metric, but we still prioritise **recall** because missing heart disease is dangerous.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"disease_rate = df[TARGET].mean()\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Disease rate: {disease_rate:.1%}\\\")\\n\", \"print(f\\\"No-disease rate: {1 - disease_rate:.1%}\\\")\\n\", \"print(f\\\"\\\\nClass counts:\\\\n{df[TARGET].value_counts()}\\\")\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 15. Train / Validation / Test Split Strategy\\n\", \"\\n\", \"We use a stratified 65/15/20 split. With only ~303 rows, every sample counts.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"X = df.drop(columns=[TARGET])\\n\", \"y = df[TARGET]\\n\", \"\\n\", \"X_temp, X_test, y_temp, y_test = train_test_split(\\n\", \"    X, y, test_size=TEST_SIZE, random_state=SEED, stratify=y\\n\", \")\\n\", \"X_train, X_val, y_train, y_val = train_test_split(\\n\", \"    X_temp, y_temp, test_size=VAL_SIZE / (1 - TEST_SIZE),\\n\", \"    random_state=SEED, stratify=y_temp\\n\", \")\\n\", \"\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Train: {X_train.shape}  Val: {X_val.shape}  Test: {X_test.shape}\\\")\\n\", \"for name, ys in [(\\\"Train\\\", y_train), (\\\"Val\\\", y_val), (\\\"Test\\\", y_test)]:\\n\", \"    print(f\\\"{name} disease rate: {ys.mean():.3f}\\\")\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 16. Preprocessing Strategy\\n\", \"\\n\", \"**Decisions:**\\n\", \"- **Missing values:** Handled above (ca, thal imputed with median).\\n\", \"- **All features numeric:** The dataset is already integer/float-encoded.\\n\", \"- **Scaling:** StandardScaler for all features — benefits logistic regression and distance-based models; trees are invariant.\\n\", \"- **No leakage:** ColumnTransformer fit only on training data.\\n\", \"- **Categorical features:** `cp`, `restecg`, `slope`, `thal` are coded as integers but represent categories. Trees handle this natively; we keep them numeric.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"feature_cols = X_train.columns.tolist()\\n\", \"\\n\", \"preprocessor = ColumnTransformer(\\n\", \"    transformers=[(\\\"scale\\\", StandardScaler(), feature_cols)],\\n\", \"    remainder=\\\"passthrough\\\"\\n\", \")\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Features: {len(feature_cols)}\\\")\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 17. Feature Engineering\\n\", \"\\n\", \"We create a few clinical interaction features that cardiologists find meaningful.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"def engineer_features(df_in):\\n\", \"    df_out = df_in.copy()\\n\", \"    # Age × max heart rate interaction\\n\", \"    if \\\"age\\\" in df_out.columns and \\\"thalach\\\" in df_out.columns:\\n\", \"        df_out[\\\"age_thalach_ratio\\\"] = df_out[\\\"age\\\"] / df_out[\\\"thalach\\\"].clip(lower=1)\\n\", \"    # Max heart rate achieved vs age-predicted max (220 - age)\\n\", \"    if \\\"age\\\" in df_out.columns and \\\"thalach\\\" in df_out.columns:\\n\", \"        df_out[\\\"hr_reserve\\\"] = (220 - df_out[\\\"age\\\"]) - df_out[\\\"thalach\\\"]\\n\", \"    # Chest pain severity flag\\n\", \"    if \\\"cp\\\" in df_out.columns:\\n\", \"        df_out[\\\"cp_severe\\\"] = (df_out[\\\"cp\\\"] >= 2).astype(int)\\n\", \"    return df_out\\n\", \"\\n\", \"X_train = engineer_features(X_train)\\n\", \"X_val = engineer_features(X_val)\\n\", \"X_test = engineer_features(X_test)\\n\", \"\\n\", \"new_feats = [c for c in X_train.columns if c not in feature_cols]\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Engineered features: {new_feats}\\\")\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Total features: {X_train.shape[1]}\\\")\\n\", \"\\n\", \"all_features = X_train.columns.tolist()\\n\", \"preprocessor = ColumnTransformer(\\n\", \"    transformers=[(\\\"scale\\\", StandardScaler(), all_features)],\\n\", \"    remainder=\\\"passthrough\\\"\\n\", \")\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 18. Baseline Model\\n\", \"\\n\", \"DummyClassifier sets the floor. Then LogReg and Random Forest establish reasonable baselines.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"results = {}\\n\", \"\\n\", \"dummy = Pipeline([(\\\"pre\\\", preprocessor), (\\\"clf\\\", DummyClassifier(strategy=\\\"most_frequent\\\", random_state=SEED))])\\n\", \"dummy.fit(X_train, y_train)\\n\", \"results[\\\"Dummy\\\"] = {\\\"Accuracy\\\": accuracy_score(y_val, dummy.predict(X_val)), \\\"F1\\\": f1_score(y_val, dummy.predict(X_val))}\\n\", \"print(\\\"Dummy:\\\", {k: f\\\"{v:.4f}\\\" for k, v in results[\\\"Dummy\\\"].items()})\\n\", \"\\n\", \"lr = Pipeline([(\\\"pre\\\", preprocessor), (\\\"clf\\\", LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000, random_state=SEED))])\\n\", \"lr.fit(X_train, y_train)\\n\", \"y_prob_lr = lr.predict_proba(X_val)[:, 1]\\n\", \"results[\\\"LogReg\\\"] = {\\\"Accuracy\\\": accuracy_score(y_val, lr.predict(X_val)), \\\"F1\\\": f1_score(y_val, lr.predict(X_val)),\\n\", \"                     \\\"Recall\\\": recall_score(y_val, lr.predict(X_val)), \\\"ROC-AUC\\\": roc_auc_score(y_val, y_prob_lr)}\\n\", \"print(\\\"LogReg:\\\", {k: f\\\"{v:.4f}\\\" for k, v in results[\\\"LogReg\\\"].items()})\\n\", \"\\n\", \"rf = Pipeline([(\\\"pre\\\", preprocessor), (\\\"clf\\\", RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=200, random_state=SEED, n_jobs=-1))])\\n\", \"rf.fit(X_train, y_train)\\n\", \"y_prob_rf = rf.predict_proba(X_val)[:, 1]\\n\", \"results[\\\"RF\\\"] = {\\\"Accuracy\\\": accuracy_score(y_val, rf.predict(X_val)), \\\"F1\\\": f1_score(y_val, rf.predict(X_val)),\\n\", \"                 \\\"Recall\\\": recall_score(y_val, rf.predict(X_val)), \\\"ROC-AUC\\\": roc_auc_score(y_val, y_prob_rf)}\\n\", \"print(\\\"RF:\\\", {k: f\\\"{v:.4f}\\\" for k, v in results[\\\"RF\\\"].items()})\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 19. LazyPredict Benchmark\\n\", \"\\n\", \"LazyPredict fits ~30 classifiers quickly. With only ~303 rows, high variance is expected.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"X_train_lp = preprocessor.fit_transform(X_train)\\n\", \"X_val_lp = preprocessor.transform(X_val)\\n\", \"\\n\", \"lazy = LazyClassifier(verbose=0, ignore_warnings=True, random_state=SEED)\\n\", \"models_lp, _ = lazy.fit(X_train_lp, X_val_lp, y_train, y_val)\\n\", \"print(\\\"Top 15 models:\\\")\\n\", \"models_lp.head(15)\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 20. FLAML AutoML Run\\n\", \"\\n\", \"FLAML optimises for F1 — balancing precision and recall for medical diagnosis.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"automl = AutoML()\\n\", \"X_train_fl = preprocessor.fit_transform(X_train)\\n\", \"X_val_fl = preprocessor.transform(X_val)\\n\", \"\\n\", \"automl.fit(\\n\", \"    X_train_fl, y_train,\\n\", \"    task=\\\"classification\\\",\\n\", \"    metric=\\\"f1\\\",\\n\", \"    time_budget=FLAML_BUDGET,\\n\", \"    seed=SEED,\\n\", \"    verbose=0,\\n\", \")\\n\", \"\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Best model: {automl.best_estimator}\\\")\\n\", \"y_pred_fl = automl.predict(X_val_fl)\\n\", \"y_prob_fl = automl.predict_proba(X_val_fl)[:, 1]\\n\", \"results[\\\"FLAML\\\"] = {\\\"Accuracy\\\": accuracy_score(y_val, y_pred_fl), \\\"F1\\\": f1_score(y_val, y_pred_fl),\\n\", \"                    \\\"Recall\\\": recall_score(y_val, y_pred_fl), \\\"ROC-AUC\\\": roc_auc_score(y_val, y_prob_fl)}\\n\", \"print(\\\"FLAML:\\\", {k: f\\\"{v:.4f}\\\" for k, v in results[\\\"FLAML\\\"].items()})\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 21. Top 3 Model Selection\\n\", \"\\n\", \"Based on LazyPredict and FLAML results, we select three strong model families:\\n\", \"1. **LightGBM / ExtraTrees** — often top performers\\n\", \"2. **XGBoost / AdaBoost** — gradient boosting alternative\\n\", \"3. **Logistic Regression** — often competitive on small clinical datasets due to low variance\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"try:\\n\", \"    from lightgbm import LGBMClassifier\\n\", \"    has_lgbm = True\\n\", \"except ImportError:\\n\", \"    has_lgbm = False\\n\", \"try:\\n\", \"    from xgboost import XGBClassifier\\n\", \"    has_xgb = True\\n\", \"except ImportError:\\n\", \"    has_xgb = False\\n\", \"\\n\", \"top3 = {}\\n\", \"if has_lgbm:\\n\", \"    top3[\\\"LightGBM\\\"] = LGBMClassifier(n_estimators=200, learning_rate=0.05, max_depth=3, random_state=SEED, verbose=-1)\\n\", \"else:\\n\", \"    from sklearn.ensemble import ExtraTreesClassifier\\n\", \"    top3[\\\"ExtraTrees\\\"] = ExtraTreesClassifier(n_estimators=200, random_state=SEED, n_jobs=-1)\\n\", \"\\n\", \"if has_xgb:\\n\", \"    top3[\\\"XGBoost\\\"] = XGBClassifier(n_estimators=200, learning_rate=0.05, max_depth=3, random_state=SEED, verbosity=0)\\n\", \"else:\\n\", \"    from sklearn.ensemble import AdaBoostClassifier\\n\", \"    top3[\\\"AdaBoost\\\"] = AdaBoostClassifier(n_estimators=150, random_state=SEED)\\n\", \"\\n\", \"top3[\\\"LogisticRegression\\\"] = LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000, C=0.5, random_state=SEED)\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Top 3: {list(top3.keys())}\\\")\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 22. Final Training and Evaluation of Top 3\\n\", \"\\n\", \"We train on the full training set and evaluate on the held-out test set.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"X_train_t = preprocessor.fit_transform(X_train)\\n\", \"X_val_t = preprocessor.transform(X_val)\\n\", \"X_test_t = preprocessor.transform(X_test)\\n\", \"\\n\", \"final_results = {}\\n\", \"for name, model in top3.items():\\n\", \"    model.fit(X_train_t, y_train)\\n\", \"    y_pred = model.predict(X_test_t)\\n\", \"    y_prob = model.predict_proba(X_test_t)[:, 1]\\n\", \"    final_results[name] = {\\n\", \"        \\\"Accuracy\\\": accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred),\\n\", \"        \\\"Precision\\\": precision_score(y_test, y_pred),\\n\", \"        \\\"Recall\\\": recall_score(y_test, y_pred),\\n\", \"        \\\"F1\\\": f1_score(y_test, y_pred),\\n\", \"        \\\"ROC-AUC\\\": roc_auc_score(y_test, y_prob),\\n\", \"        \\\"PR-AUC\\\": average_precision_score(y_test, y_prob),\\n\", \"    }\\n\", \"    print(f\\\"\\\\n{name}:\\\")\\n\", \"    print(classification_report(y_test, y_pred, target_names=[\\\"No Disease\\\", \\\"Disease\\\"]))\\n\", \"\\n\", \"results_df = pd.DataFrame(final_results).T\\n\", \"print(\\\"\\\\n=== Final Test Results ===\\\")\\n\", \"results_df\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, len(top3), figsize=(5*len(top3), 4))\\nif len(top3) == 1: axes = [axes]\\nfor ax, (name, model) in zip(axes, top3.items()):\\n    ConfusionMatrixDisplay.from_predictions(y_test, model.predict(X_test_t), ax=ax, cmap=\\\"Blues\\\", display_labels=[\\\"No Disease\\\",\\\"Disease\\\"])\\n    ax.set_title(name)\\nplt.suptitle(\\\"Confusion Matrices — Test Set\\\", y=1.02)\\nplt.tight_layout()\\nplt.show()\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(14, 5))\\nfor name, model in top3.items():\\n    RocCurveDisplay.from_estimator(model, X_test_t, y_test, ax=axes[0], name=name)\\n    PrecisionRecallDisplay.from_estimator(model, X_test_t, y_test, ax=axes[1], name=name)\\naxes[0].plot([0,1],[0,1],\\\"k--\\\",alpha=0.5)\\naxes[0].set_title(\\\"ROC Curves\\\")\\naxes[1].set_title(\\\"PR Curves\\\")\\nplt.tight_layout()\\nplt.show()\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 23. Error Analysis\\n\", \"\\n\", \"We examine misclassifications — especially **false negatives** (missed heart disease cases).\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"best_name = list(top3.keys())[0]\\nbest_model = top3[best_name]\\ny_pred_best = best_model.predict(X_test_t)\\n\\nfn_mask = (y_test == 1) & (y_pred_best == 0)\\nfp_mask = (y_test == 0) & (y_pred_best == 1)\\nprint(f\\\"False Negatives (missed disease): {fn_mask.sum()}\\\")\\nprint(f\\\"False Positives (false alarms): {fp_mask.sum()}\\\")\\nprint(f\\\"Sensitivity (recall): {recall_score(y_test, y_pred_best):.1%}\\\")\\n\\ntest_df = X_test.copy()\\ntest_df[\\\"error_type\\\"] = \\\"correct\\\"\\ntest_df.loc[fn_mask.values, \\\"error_type\\\"] = \\\"false_negative\\\"\\ntest_df.loc[fp_mask.values, \\\"error_type\\\"] = \\\"false_positive\\\"\\n\\nfor col in [\\\"age\\\", \\\"thalach\\\", \\\"oldpeak\\\", \\\"cp\\\"]:\\n    if col in test_df.columns:\\n        print(f\\\"\\\\n{col} — mean by error type:\\\")\\n        print(test_df.groupby(\\\"error_type\\\")[col].mean())\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 24. Interpretation and Business Insight\\n\", \"\\n\", \"**Key findings:**\\n\", \"1. **Chest pain type (cp)** — atypical and non-anginal pain correlate with disease presence.\\n\", \"2. **Maximum heart rate (thalach)** — lower max HR during exercise is strongly associated with disease.\\n\", \"3. **ST depression (oldpeak)** — higher values indicate exercise-induced ischaemia.\\n\", \"4. **Number of major vessels (ca)** — more coloured vessels correlate with disease.\\n\", \"5. **Thalassemia type** — reversible defects are a strong predictor.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"**Clinical recommendations:**\\n\", \"- Use the model as a **screening tool**, not a diagnostic replacement.\\n\", \"- Patients flagged positive should receive further testing (angiography, stress test).\\n\", \"- Lower the classification threshold to increase sensitivity in screening contexts.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 25. Limitations\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. **Small dataset:** Only ~303 rows — high variance in model estimates.\\n\", \"2. **Single centre:** Cleveland data only — may not generalise to other populations.\\n\", \"3. **Historical data:** Collected in the 1980s — medical practices have evolved.\\n\", \"4. **Feature encoding:** Integer codes for categorical clinical variables lose some nuance.\\n\", \"5. **No imaging data:** Real cardiology uses ECGs, echocardiograms, CT scans.\\n\", \"6. **Binary simplification:** Original dataset has 5-class severity; we binarised to disease/no-disease.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 26. How to Improve This Project\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. **Cross-validation:** Use 5-fold or 10-fold CV for more reliable estimates.\\n\", \"2. **Multi-class:** Predict disease severity (0-4) instead of binary.\\n\", \"3. **Multiple centres:** Combine Cleveland, Hungarian, Swiss, VA datasets.\\n\", \"4. **Threshold tuning:** Optimise for sensitivity ≥ 95% (medical screening standard).\\n\", \"5. **SHAP explanations:** Individual patient-level feature importance.\\n\", \"6. **Ensemble methods:** Stack models for robustness.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 27. Production Considerations\\n\", \"\\n\", \"- **Clinical validation:** Model must pass prospective clinical trial before deployment.\\n\", \"- **Regulatory approval:** Medical AI requires FDA/CE marking (SaMD classification).\\n\", \"- **Integration:** Deploy as clinical decision support within EHR systems.\\n\", \"- **Monitoring:** Track sensitivity and specificity on new patient cohorts.\\n\", \"- **Explainability:** Clinicians need per-patient explanations (SHAP, LIME).\\n\", \"- **Bias audit:** Validate across age, sex, and ethnicity groups.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 28. Common Mistakes\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. **Prioritising accuracy over recall** — missing a heart disease patient is far worse than a false alarm.\\n\", \"2. **Not handling the binarisation** of the 5-class target properly.\\n\", \"3. **Treating integer-coded categoricals** (cp, thal) as continuous without awareness.\\n\", \"4. **Overfitting on 303 rows** — complex models memorise noise.\\n\", \"5. **Ignoring cross-validation** — single splits on tiny datasets are unreliable.\\n\", \"6. **Claiming clinical readiness** without prospective validation.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 29. Mini Challenge / Exercises\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. **Sensitivity target:** Tune the threshold to achieve ≥ 95% recall. What happens to precision?\\n\", \"2. **Multi-class:** Use the original 5-class target. How does performance change?\\n\", \"3. **Feature selection:** Remove the weakest features. Does performance improve with fewer features?\\n\", \"4. **Clinical rules:** Compare model performance against simple clinical rules (e.g., cp + oldpeak threshold).\\n\", \"5. **SHAP:** Add SHAP waterfall plots for 3 individual patients — one TP, one FN, one FP.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 30. Final Summary / Key Takeaways\\n\", \"\\n\", \"| Aspect | Detail |\\n\", \"|---|---|\\n\", \"| **Task** | Binary classification — heart disease prediction |\\n\", \"| **Dataset** | ~303 patients, 13 clinical features, ~54% disease rate |\\n\", \"| **Best metric focus** | F1 and Recall (medical screening) |\\n\", \"| **Baseline** | DummyClassifier ~54% accuracy |\\n\", \"| **Key insight** | thalach, cp, oldpeak, and ca are the strongest clinical predictors |\\n\", \"| **Limitation** | Very small, single-centre 1980s data |\\n\", \"\\n\", \"**What you learned:**\\n\", \"- How to work with clinical/medical datasets\\n\", \"- Why recall (sensitivity) matters more than accuracy in medical diagnosis\\n\", \"- How to handle small datasets with proper validation strategies\\n\", \"- The full benchmark → AutoML → top 3 evaluation pipeline\\n\", \"- Clinical ML considerations: explainability, fairness, regulatory requirements\"]\n",
    "  }\n",
    " ]\n",
    "}\n"
